  <prompt>
    Filed 2026-05-27 during R4 final review #3. Operator review of residuals identified two
    items quick + cheap to clear before 090 wrap-up: (1) a real production bug surfaced by
    the CommandBar test crash, (2) the master-level deploy-artifact tracking issue that R4
    task 060 fixed locally but didn't reach master.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke close-out engineer. Surgical defensive fixes.
  </role>

  <goal>
    (1) `useKeyboardShortcuts` no longer crashes when `commands` is undefined.
    (2) `deploy/api-publish/*` is untracked from git on the R4 branch (durable fix
    that will reach master via merge).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      **Fix 1: useKeyboardShortcuts TypeError**

      Source: `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/hooks/useKeyboardShortcuts.ts`
      Line 32 (runtime): `commands.find(cmd => cmd.keyboardShortcut === shortcut)`

      The hook destructures `const { commands, context, enabled = true } = options;` with
      no default for `commands`. TypeScript marks `commands: ICommand[]` as required, but
      cannot enforce at runtime — a consumer rendering before its command list is loaded
      (e.g., async fetch path) crashes the app with
      `TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'find')`.

      This crash blocked the `CommandBar.test.tsx` suite (23 tests) from running entirely.
      It was first flagged by task 074 sub-agent ("verified pre-existing"), again by 077,
      and again by 078. Per task 078 memo §carry-over recommendation: "Real bug to address
      in a follow-up."

      Fix: defensive default `const { commands = [], context, enabled = true } = options;`
      `[].find(...)` returns undefined cleanly, hook becomes a no-op.

      **Fix 2: deploy artifact tracking**

      `.gitignore` line 122 has `deploy/` rule, but 272 files in `deploy/api-publish/*`
      were tracked in git BEFORE the rule was added. Once tracked, `.gitignore` cannot
      untrack — only `git rm --cached` does.

      R4 task 060 (B-1) ran `git rm --cached -r deploy/api-publish/` on the R4 branch,
      but the fix never reached master. Other projects (auth-v2, BFF remediation,
      matter-ui-r1) re-tracked the files during their deploys. When R4 synced master on
      2026-05-27, those files came back tracked.

      Fix: re-run `git rm --cached -r deploy/api-publish/` on the R4 branch. After
      merge-to-master, master inherits the untracking. Then `.gitignore` actually works —
      `git add deploy/api-publish/...` is ignored unless deliberate `-f` override.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/hooks/useKeyboardShortcuts.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/PageChrome/__tests__/CommandBar.test.tsx</file>
      <file>deploy/api-publish/ (272 tracked files; .gitignore line 122 covers)</file>
      <file>.gitignore</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">Fix 1 must be defensive — no runtime behavior change for valid inputs (only graceful handling of undefined).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Fix 2 must not delete files from disk — `git rm --cached` only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">After fixes: BFF build still clean. UI.Components tests still pass. No new failures.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
